Class BlockList<I,D>

    I - input symbol type

    IntrusiveListElem<AbstractBaseDTNode<I,D>>, Serializable, Iterable<AbstractBaseDTNode<I,D>>

    public class BlockList<I,D>
extends IntrusiveList<AbstractBaseDTNode<I,D>>
    A list for storing blocks (identified by their root AbstractBaseDTNodes). The list is implemented as a singly-linked list, and allows O(1) insertion and removal of elements.
    Author:
    Malte Isberner

        public void insertBlock(AbstractBaseDTNode<I,D> blockRoot)
        Inserts a block into the list. Currently, the block is inserted at the head of the list. However, callers should not rely on this.
        Parameters:
        blockRoot - the root node of the block to be inserted
